To improve the data model for `aggregated_data_entity`, we can create a schema that defines the structure and constraints of the aggregated data. Here’s a suggested schema for the `aggregated_data_entity` based on typical data aggregation use cases:

### Suggested Schema for `aggregated_data_entity`

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Aggregated Data Entity",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "aggregated_data_id": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier for the aggregated data."
    },
    "generated_at": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "Timestamp when the aggregated data was generated."
    },
    "report_title": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Title of the aggregated report."
    },
    "summary": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "total_entries": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Total number of entries processed."
        },
        "successful_ingests": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Number of successful data ingests."
        },
        "failed_ingests": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Number of failed data ingests."
        },
        "percentage_success": {
          "type": "number",
          "format": "float",
          "description": "Percentage of successful ingests."
        }
      },
      "required": ["total_entries", "successful_ingests", "failed_ingests", "percentage_success"]
    },
    "details": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "active_brp_codes": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "description": "List of BRP codes that are active."
        },
        "inactive_brp_codes": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "description": "List of BRP codes that are inactive."
        }
      },
      "required": ["active_brp_codes", "inactive_brp_codes"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["aggregated_data_id", "generated_at", "report_title", "summary", "details"]
}
```

### Key Features of the Updated Schema:
- **Unique Identifier**: `aggregated_data_id` to ensure that each aggregated data entry is unique.
- **Timestamps**: `generated_at` to track when the data was aggregated.
- **Summary Section**: Includes metrics such as `total_entries`, `successful_ingests`, `failed_ingests`, and `percentage_success` for performance tracking.
- **Details Section**: Categorizes BRP codes into active and inactive lists for better data integrity and status tracking.

This schema provides a clearer structure and a more robust representation of the aggregated data. If the user has any additional suggestions or specific requirements, please let me know to make further adjustments.